This paper deals with measuring coherence in text, which is a common problem in natural language processing. The use of WordNet and unsupervised learning techniques suggests that this paper may fall under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of topic modeling and relatedness measures suggests that this paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computation and language (cs.CC).
